race.comment: VOVO (13) was unlucky not to have broken through in her brief maiden preparation but quickly made amends leading and belting the Gold Coast Maidens by 8.5L first-up. She was backed into the red and the promising mare will be further improved. Maps well and Thompson sticking is a decent push for her chances. ADRANOS (1) is in the premier stable and is busting to win. There was only 1L in it at Eagle Farm last time and Maloney has won on the gelding and replaces Thompson. GAMBINO (3) peaks off a near miss in stronger at Eagle Farm and should enjoy a soft run. Has to be considered. LIVALITTLE (6) and SAN GABRIEL (8) both present off tough first-up efforts and are in the mix as well.
